  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝirsu , Enlil’s warrior ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.3",
      "line_range": "3",
      "translation": "(i 3) When Ninĝirsu chose him from Ĝirnun in his holy heart , and decided his fate from the E-ninnu , and Nanše looked at him with favour from Sirara , then En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , given strength by Enlil , nourished on rich milk by Ninhursaĝa , chosen by Nanše in the heart , chief governor of Ninĝirsu , the child born to Lugal-Uruba , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , built a weir on the Lumagin-dug canal for Ninĝirsu with the use of 648000 fired bricks and 1840 standard gur of bitumen ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(iv 9) He fashioned ... of Ninĝirsu ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.39",
      "line_range": "39",
      "translation": "(v 2) He released ( the people of ) Lagaš , let the mother return to ( her ) child , and let the child return to ( its ) mother . He let ... return ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.47",
      "line_range": "47",
      "translation": "(vi 2) Since he built a weir on the Lumagin-dug canal in the Gu-edena for him , Ninĝirsu will care about En-metena's good fame forever ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.56",
      "line_range": "56",
      "translation": "(vi 11) Enmetena , ... by Ninĝirsu , built a weir on the Lumagin-dug canal for Ninĝirsu , his master who loves him , and named it for his sake \" Ninĝirsu ...\"."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.67",
      "line_range": "67",
      "translation": "(viii 3) The personal god of E-ana-tum , the builder of Ninĝirsu's dam , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001108.72",
      "line_range": "72",
      "translation": "(viii 8) At that time Dudu was the temple administrator of Ninĝirsu ."
    }
  ],
